              "faqs_content": "Very few, if any, African Americans are 100% African. During the period of slavery in the Americas, white men (slave traders, slave owners, etc.) often fathered children with enslaved women. Their offspring then had both African and European ancestry. This means that the descendants of the offspring will have a European branch in their family tree. There is an 8% chance that your maternal ancestry result will not be African. <span style='letter-spacing: normal;'>Read more about <a href='https://africanancestry.com/blogs/news/the-hard-truth-about-the-65'>why here</a>.</span>"
            }
        },
        {
